Create a table for students:


CREATE TABLE students (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(255),
  age INT
);
Create a table for teachers:


CREATE TABLE teachers (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(255),
  subject VARCHAR(255)
);
CRUD Operations:

Create a new student:


INSERT INTO students (id, name, email, age)
VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 'john.doe@example.com', 20);
Read student information:


SELECT * FROM students;
Update student information:


UPDATE students
SET name = 'Jane Smith', age = 22
WHERE id = 1;
Delete a student:


DELETE FROM students
WHERE id = 1;
Create a new teacher:


INSERT INTO teachers (id, name, email, subject)
VALUES (1, 'Jane Smith', 'jane.smith@example.com', 'Mathematics');
Read teacher information:


SELECT * FROM teachers;
Update teacher information:


UPDATE teachers
SET name = 'John Doe', subject = 'Physics'
WHERE id = 1;
Delete a teacher:


DELETE FROM teachers
WHERE id = 1;
